text:
reclaim the night!
.
if you can get to gloucester next friday night please march with us!  everyone is welcome regardless of age or gender and the route is accessible.
.
🌟march to support the elimination of violence against women and girls.
🌟march for change.
🌟march for the women and girls of the future.
🌟 march against the perpetuation of rape myths
🌟march in solidarity with victims and survivors.
🌟march for yourself.
🌟march to shine a light on sexual violence and abuse - raise awareness & educate.
🌟 whatever your reason, march with us!
.

text:
como extraer del estante el lomo de un libro, a veces, son los pequeños gestos cotidianos los que originan los grandes cambios. 
queremos celebrar con vosotr#s el #díadelaslibrerías regalándoos algo muy especial que hemos preparado inspirado en #acción #contradicción #revolución. si deslizáis hacia la derecha, podéis ver unas pegatinas con frases extraídas del libro que os invitamos a que las llevéis bien visibles, porque como dice @cervantesfaqs "la inactividad no es propia de una revolución".
*
para tod#s aquell#s que compréis el libro hoy en cualquier librería física del país, tendréis de regalo los 3 modelos de pegatina. solo tenéis que enviarnos un mail a info@copelia.xyz con una foto de vuestro ticket de compra y vuestros datos y os las enviaremos a casa. 
feliz #díadelaslibrerías

text: διαβάζω άρθρο ότι στην ιρλανδία κρίθηκε αθώος ένας βιαστής και αναμεσα σε διαφορα η υπερασπιση του κατηγορουμένου είπε και το ότι η κοπέλα φόραγε στρινγκ. προτού λοιπόν τα μαζέψω και μεταναστεύσω σε ένα έρημο νησί, θα ήθελα να ποστάρω αυτο εδώ το τρου στόρι, το οποίο εμφανίστηκε στην τελευταια (αυτο)έκδοση του κόμικ, ως εξτραδάκι.. μου συνέβη όντως το τελευταίο καρέ, ακριβώς όπως το βλέπετε. για να τελειώνουμε: αν κάποια/ος ντύνεται σέξι δε μας αφορά, μπορεί να θέλει να τραβήξει τα βλέμματα (καλώς ή κακώς δεν είναι αυτό το θέμα μας) ή να θέλει όντως σεξ. αλλά καμια και κανεις δε θέλει να τον βάλουν κατω και να του δώσουν μια από τις χειρότερες εμπειρίες που μπορεί να βιώσει άνθρωπος. κατά τα άλλα, συχνά δεν έχει καν σημασία τι φοράς. η καφρίλα θα σου συμβεί ακόμα κι αν φοράς ράσα. #metoo #catcalling #nohope
name: Dimitra Adamopoulou

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
the silence of the girls~ pat barker
*
"i do what no man before me has ever done, i kiss the hands of the man who killed my son,” says priam when he begs for hector’s body.
*
but in our moment of pity for the great priam who is begging his sons murderer for his defiled body, he never for a moment turns that same glance at briseis and the other slaves in the camp who are now raped by the men who take have murdered their own families and taken them from the status of women to objects. priam is resigned to his daughters fates he refuses to try and take briseis back with him, she is not worth the trouble.
*
pat barker is a good writer, and conveys a sense of timelessness in her story –the timelessness experienced by a slave for whom nothing changes until she is passed on to a new owner. aside from this, rendering of a human to an object wasn’t well done, and the repetitions seemed more forced than natural. barker could have been more subtle about this. briseis is confused about feeling pity for patroclus, and not completely hating achilles (her stockholm syndrome), but her anger at the death of her family and her new lot in life doesn’t come to surface in the slightest. while the book has some really interesting moments (such as the execution of polyxena and her hair being cut), the rest was a superficial blur.
*
i appreciated the fact that the gods were seen to be real entities, and that the plight of women was nothing of significance to them –a hopeless note that women did not matter even to them. but even so, barker could have been more considerate of the language she used; i get that achilles is a man-child, but him shouting “mummy, mummy” into the water seems a bit out of place.
*
as someone who loved circe by madeline miller and was really looking forward to this retelling, i was left disappointed.
*

aus dem aktuellen band “die vierte welle!? feminismus heute”. der neue feminismus der gegenwart gehört zur popkultur und ist geradezu zum mainstream für eine jüngere frauengeneration geworden. was hat sich seit den frühen wellen der bewegung getan und wie sieht der feminismus heute aus, gerade im kontext der kunst? .
.
.

text:
i. you say,
you can't wait to be 20,
and find peace,
 in beer bottles like your dad does.

ii. you say,
you found love last night.

iii. you were 14,
when you first found love.

and you didn't know back then, 
love is like paris in 1789,
nobody leaves not angry, 
nobody leaves not a rebel.

love is like russia, 
in revolution.

hand grenades in your pocket, 
timebomb in your back pack.

you're here only to break a few homes.

steal rum off of your daddy's bar,
burn cigarettes in the back of your car.

you're so young and angry, 
you need to be hollow,
to set free.

so all you do is go on war.

keep your love 
like sodium in your hand,
burn your beloved 
everytime he gasps for air.

your throat will burn,
as if you swallowed,
a bottle of hcl,

everytime you say i love you.

and so you'll swallow lies,
like ice cream sunades,
from your childhood,
that you had,
in your favourite alley.

when your wrists were skin,
and all you did,
was collect popsicle sticks.
(now all you do is collect broken 
architecture and hang it around your neck)

iv. you were 16,
when you first fell out of love.

there are curses
and love potions on your floor.

home is not like how he left it,

with daisies and chocolate cakes,

it's full of 
hair that you cut 
and forgot to drain (he was on your mind)

poems you didn't write
(you didn't want him out of your mind)

v. you've been in and out 
of love,

you've tatsed the blood 
on both sides.

yet you're going in again,

you feel this is different,

you're 17.

vi. you're 20 
you came home last night 
your masacra was a mess,

you've emptied 
five beer bottles tonight,
you've still not fallen out of it.
.
.
utopaingrey.
(@utopiangrey)
.
.
.

text:
women have been protesting for decades!!!!
from the the suffrage movement in the early 1900’s to the equal rights amendment marches in the 70’s/80’s to the me too revolution happening right now. we have always been fighters and we will continue to fight and stand up for our rights. we need to fight not only for ourselves but for the people that can’t fight, those whose voices will never be heard, for the environment and every little creature in it. its up to us to make the difference.

text:
håll i hatten. detta sker alltså i nuläget, i cirkusen kring virtanens anmälan och åtal mot mig ang grovt förtal. häng med nu, detta börjar nämligen alltmer likna en stieg larsson-roman.
👇
förra hösten i och med mitt outande av virtanen, och #metoo så inledde @aftonbladet en omfattande internutredning. en utomstående person, kvinna som tidigare jobbat som utredare hos polisen, togs in av ab för att gräva i olika anklagelser mot virtanen. hon ringde upp mig en dag förra hösten och vi hade ett långt samtal (som jag såhär i efterhand inser att jag borde spelat in) där hon berättade att hon hittat ”mycket” på fv, flera grova övergrepp och även i nutid och att hon höll på att sammanställa allt för att rapportera till aftonbladet. kort därefter blev han utköpt därifrån, för miljonbelopp. nu när han drar mig inför rätta (för mina och era skattepengar) så vill jag givetvis ha en så rättvis rättegång som möjligt. därför vill jag och min advokat styrka min berättelse och mina skäl till att hänga ut honom, genom att visa på att han under många år begått flertalet övergrepp på unga tjejer. vi har begärt att aftonbladet ska lämna ut sin internutredning (givetvis utan att röja källor) och att internutredaren ska höras i rätten. men nu påstår alltså aftonbladet på fullaste allvar att de ”inte har några exemplar kvar av utredningen”. tjena. flertalet chefer på tidningen delgavs vad internutredaren kom fram till. jag vet flera kvinnor som pratat med internutredaren och berättat för henne om virtanens övergrepp. vad är det aftonbladet vill dölja? varför sätter man annars munkavle på alla som kan vittna? fanns det bara ett pappers-exemplar av en dyr och omfattande utredning (om en av tidningens största profiler som jobbat där i två decenniet) som tyvärr råkat strimlas i en dokumentförstörare? nej. givetvis inte.
varför skyddar ”vi gillar olika” och på många andra vis utåt sett politiskt korrekta aftonbladet och schibsted en sexualförbrytare? lyssna på hela reportaget på @ekotsverigesradio s sida.
name: Cissi Wallin

håll i hatten. detta sker alltså i nuläget, i cirkusen kring virtanens anmälan och åtal mot mig ang grovt förtal. häng med nu, detta börjar nämligen alltmer likna en stieg larsson-roman.
👇
förra hösten i och med mitt outande av virtanen, och #metoo så inledde @aftonbladet en omfattande internutredning. en utomstående person, kvinna som tidigare jobbat som utredare hos polisen, togs in av ab för att gräva i olika anklagelser mot virtanen. hon ringde upp mig en dag förra hösten och vi hade ett långt samtal (som jag såhär i efterhand inser att jag borde spelat in) där hon berättade att hon hittat ”mycket” på fv, flera grova övergrepp och även i nutid och att hon höll på att sammanställa allt för att rapportera till aftonbladet. kort därefter blev han utköpt därifrån, för miljonbelopp. nu när han drar mig inför rätta (för mina och era skattepengar) så vill jag givetvis ha en så rättvis rättegång som möjligt. därför vill jag och min advokat styrka min berättelse och mina skäl till att hänga ut honom, genom att visa på att han under många år begått flertalet övergrepp på unga tjejer. vi har begärt att aftonbladet ska lämna ut sin internutredning (givetvis utan att röja källor) och att internutredaren ska höras i rätten. men nu påstår alltså aftonbladet på fullaste allvar att de ”inte har några exemplar kvar av utredningen”. tjena. flertalet chefer på tidningen delgavs vad internutredaren kom fram till. jag vet flera kvinnor som pratat med internutredaren och berättat för henne om virtanens övergrepp. vad är det aftonbladet vill dölja? varför sätter man annars munkavle på alla som kan vittna? fanns det bara ett pappers-exemplar av en dyr och omfattande utredning (om en av tidningens största profiler som jobbat där i två decenniet) som tyvärr råkat strimlas i en dokumentförstörare? nej. givetvis inte.
varför skyddar ”vi gillar olika” och på många andra vis utåt sett politiskt korrekta aftonbladet och schibsted en sexualförbrytare? lyssna på hela reportaget på @ekotsverigesradio s sida.

#thisisnotconsent 
je crois qu'on a atteint le pire niveau d'idiotie. 
en irlande, un homme a été acquitté grace à un string. en effet, accusé de viol sur une femme de 17ans, un homme a été liberé sous prétexte que la jeunne fille portait un string. donc, il serait normal de violer des femmes parce qu'elles ont de le lingerie dite sexy ? libérer un homme, le déclarer non coupable car une femme de 17 ans portait un string ? il est donc lorgique et banal de passer outre la volonté de quelqu'un, de le forcer à avoir des rapports car un sous-vêtement est considéré comme un provocateur ? 
où va le monde ? dit-on d'un homme qu'il est provocateur parce qu'il porte un slip, un boxeur? 
on est arrivé à un point culminant dans le manque d'humanité. cette jeune fille a déjà du se sentir humilier par cet homme et maintenant, ca ne pose pas de problème a ce qu'on expose sa lingerie. depuis quand le métier d'avocat signifie être sans coeur et sans émotions ? tout le monde a le droit d'être défendu, mais certains sont indéfendables.

le non d'une femme ne peut en aucun cas être remis en cause par sa lingerie

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

pre_proc_tweet:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitba doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subve elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
제목: 미투 (with you) - 사건 경위; 본인은 밤9시에서 10시경, 쌍문동의 이자카야에서 친구들과 술을 마시고 있었음. 본인은 열라게 맛있는 술을 타주며 분위기를 의도치 않게 띄우고 있었음. (tmi?) 그러던 찰나, 한 여성 친구(이하 w양)가 본인에게 이런 말을 하였음. "솔아, 너 아직도 왕자있어? 보여줘봐~ 아니다 그냥 넌 벗고 마셔라!" 라는 말을 하였음. 그 말을 듣자마자 본인은, 수치심과 모욕적인 언사로 인해 온몸이 얼어버렸고, 아무말도 하지 못 한채로 덜덜덜 떨며, 고양이 잃어버린 소녀마냥 울어버렸음. 그 정신적인 충격은 지금까지도 유지되고 있으며, 이에 정식으로 미투함. 사과를 하지 않으면 fbi와 cia 그리고 월스트릿저널과 로이터통신에 제보하겠음. / 
미투 운동의 가장 중요한 요소인; 과장과 허위사실 기재의 원칙에 따라 작성하였음. 왜냐면 미투 운동은 사실관계를 먼저 따지기 보다, 피해자의 말을 우선으로 듣는 아주 좋은 운동이니까 (^_^) 근데 w양이 저 말 한 것은 진짜임.

난 위에 장난식으로 미투 운동을 했지만, 미투 운동이라는게 있다고 한다. me too 인지 you too인지 with you 인지 without you인지 뭔지 하여간 그런게 있다고 한다. me too! 하면 with you!! 라고 해야 한다고 한다. (힙합?) 저게 뭔지 관심도 없다. 성(sex) 상품의 메카인 할리우드에서 저런 운동이 나왔다는 것 자체가 어불성설이기 때문이다. 권력이나 지위를 통해서 성희롱이나 성폭행을 당했다면, 우선적으로 증거물 채집 후; 그 자리에서 바로 신고 하여야한다. 대중 매체에 나와서 떠들어대기 전에 말이다. 그게 진짜라면 말이다. 그 당시 경황이 없어서 우물쭈물 댔다는 건 핑계에 불과하다. 어떻게 사람이 그렇게 이성적일 수 가 있냐고? 그럼 그런 급박한 상황에서 감성적일 것인가? 바로 신고하지 못했다면, 아마 부모나 학교의 성교육 부재가 원인이 될 수 있다고 생각한다. 물론 미투 운동으로 인한 긍정적인 효과도 많았고, 사회 분위기도 조금이나마 바뀌었으며, 벌 받을 사람들은 늦게나마 벌을 받았다. 그리고 지위와 권력을 이용해서 성폭행을 한 사람들은 개새끼다. 근데 그걸 역으로 악용하는 사람도 개새끼다. 
사실 미투 운동을 하라고 하면, 내가 할게 수두룩 빽빽삑삑뽁뽁뿡하게 많다. 일터에서 누가봐도 고의로 엉덩이 쓰다듬고 가고, 팔 만지고, 옷 벗고 일하라는 둥, 하루에도 수십번씩 성희롱이 오갔었다. 특히 지하철은 누가 만지는 지도 모르고 당한적도 있다. 그럴 때마다 난 장난은 장난으로 받아들이고, 좀 심하다 싶으면 이러지 마시라고 말을 했다. 미투를 하는게 아니라 말이다. /

결론: 나는 w양의 석고대죄와 더불어 300만원을 입금할것을 요!청!한다. 사실은 이랬다. 그녀가 나에게 성적 수치심 발언을 했을때, 나는 "야! 나 미투한다!" 이랬더니, 그녀는 "해라 해." 라고 했고, 그래서 나는 했다. 
#미투  #윗유 #사진 #metoo #withyou #photo #쌍문동 #나들이 #blackedout #술

( 힙합 ? ) 저게 뭔지 관심도 없다 . 성 ( sex ) 상품의 메카인 할리우드에서 저런 운동이 나왔다는 것 자체가 어불성설이기 때문이다 . 권력이나 지위를 통해서 성희롱이나 성폭행을 당했다면 , 우선적으로 증거물 채집 후 ; 그 자리에서 바로 신고 하여야한다 . 대중 매체에 나와서 떠들어대기 전에 말이다 . 그게 진짜라면 말이다 . 그 당시 경황이 없어서 우물쭈물 댔다는 건 핑계에 불과하다 . 어떻게 사람이 그렇게 이성적일 수 가 있냐고 ? 그럼 그런 급박한 상황에서 감성적일 것인가 ? 바로 신고하지 못했다면 , 아마 부모나 학교의 성교육 부재가 원인이 될 수 있다고 생각한다 . 물론 미투 운동으로 인한 긍정적인 효과도 많았고 , 사회 분위기도 조금이나마 바뀌었으며 , 벌 받을 사람들은 늦게나마 벌을 받았다 . 그리고 지위와 권력을 이용해서 성폭행을 한 사람들은 개새끼다 . 근데 그걸 역으로 악용하는 사람도 개새끼다 . 사실 미투 운동을 하라고 하면 , 내가 할게 수두룩 빽빽삑삑뽁뽁뿡하게 많다 . 일터에서 누가봐도 고의로 엉덩이 쓰다듬고 가고 , 팔 만지고 , 옷 벗고 일하라는 둥 , 하루에도 수십번씩 성희롱이 오갔었다 . 특히 지하철은 누가 만지는 지도 모르고 당한적도 있다 . 그럴 때마다 난 장난은 장난으로 받아들이고 , 좀 심하다 싶으면 이러지 마시라고 말을 했다 . 미투를 하는게 아니라 말이다 . / 결론 : 나는 w양의 석고대죄와 더불어 300만원을 입금할것을 요 ! 청 ! 한다 . 사실은 이랬다 . 그녀가 나에게 성적 수치심 발언을 했을때 , 나는 `` 야 ! 나 미투한다 ! '' 이랬더니 , 그녀는 `` 해라 해 . '' 라고 했고 , 그래서 나는 했다 .

text:
protests have taken place in ireland after the underwear a teenager was wearing was cited in the trial of a man accused of raping her. in the course of the trial, the defense lawyer held up a pair of the 17-year-old’s underwear in court, and asked: “you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front.” a 27-year-old man was found not guilty of raping the teenager earlier this month. the lawyer’s comments provoked immediate criticism, and women gathered at demonstrations across ireland to protest the handling of the court case on wednesday. their anger built on an online movement around #thisisnotconsent after the trial, kickstarted by the campaign group i believe her. “simply put, clothing is not consent. this kind of victim blaming is archaic and had no place in our court system,” susan dillon, who was among a group of women who started the hashtag, told buzzfeed news (📷: getty, lilthumper408, samana1988, maireos, catalanaalor via twitter)
-

[unbezahlte werbung - markennennung]

#thisisnotconsent

was ich aktuell in den nachrichten höre, schockiert mich. wir leben im jahr 2018 und noch immer werden frauen beschuldigt, sie seien für die übergriffe selbst verantwortlich.

ich kann meine wut nicht in worte fassen. als betroffene weiß ich, wieviel mut es kostet, darüber zu sprechen. die schuld- und schamgefühle sind oftmals so groß, dass die opfer lieber schweigen. sie schweigen oft aus angst. und dann gibt es diese unglaublichen, starken frauen, die nicht in schockstarre fallen und es schaffen, für sich einzustehen und zu handeln. was sie alles auf sich nehmen ist unglaublich. & dann stehen sie vor gericht und das vorgefallene wird abgetan. das opfer darf sich anhören, es sei selbst schuld gewesen. immerhin träge es ein reizvolles höschen, einen kurzen rock oder einen ausschnitt. kein erscheinungsbild, keine hautfarbe und kein kleidungsstil gibt männern das recht, grenzüberschreitend zu sein! denn nein heißt nein und das hat jeder zu akzeptieren!! und dass die worte "sie ist selbst schuld in einem gerichtssaal ausgesprochen worden, ist für mich unbegreiflich. denn jeder ist für seine taten selbst verantwortlich und niemand anders!

text:
хештеги: пользуемся правильно
⠀
спасибо, 15 плюсиков набрали, погнали ставить хештеги правильно. сохраняй пост, чтобы вернуться к нему в понедельник, сегодня все равно уже бесполезно😂
⠀
хештеги (хш) делятся на 4 группы (на самом деле их много больше):
⠀
🎯брендовые - чтобы строить бренд.
используются:
▪️для навигации: #smmekalka_боты
▪️в офлайне фоткаемся с хештегом, клиенты постят о нас: #smmekalka
▪️в инста люди по поиску могут искать не только ваш продукт, но и фирму
⠀
🔝хш ниши
высокочастотные на общую тематику. отлично индексируются в поиске, широко распространены. могут привлечь ботов и массфолловеров, но без них никак для увеличения охвата и рекомендации поста живым людям😒😏
⠀
#smm #smmпродвижение #продвижениеинстаграм
⠀
тут важно не переборщить. не ставим кучей такие хэштеги: они как создают активность, так и убивают ее🤡👻
⠀
📍хш местоположения
хоть я и работаю  клиентом из любой точки мира, но, например, хочу только с теми бизнесами, кто в москве. они и платят больше, и фотоконтент можно контролировать.
тогда я использую:
#смммосква #продвижениемосква #рекламамосква
❗️для офлайн-бизнесов - мастхэв❗️
⠀
🦊хш кампаний
хочу устроить конкурс. в правилах: сделай смешную рожицу, сфоткай, выложи. те, кто поставил хш #smmekalka_розыгрыш, автоматом участвуют. этими же хш поддерживаем актуальные тренды: #metoo
⠀
как правильно ставить?
▪️комбинируем высокочастотные хш (500к публикаций) и узконаправленные: #смм #реклама #бизнес дадут массовость, а #смммосква #сммспециалист дадут клиентов
▪️максимальное количество хш - 30
▪️хш постоянно менять, иначе инста перестанет их замечать
⠀
🔚где ставить?
▪️в самом конце поста (отделяем пробелами)
▪️в первом комментарии к посту
работает и так и так, вопрос в том, как вам больше комфортнее. я голосую за второй🙋🏻
⠀
используйте хш правильно, и они приведут вам пусть небольшой, но приток подписчиков и клиентов, а значит и денежек💸
⠀
какие еще есть вопросы по хш?
задавайте в комментариях👇

text:
the past week has easily been the most rewarding, memorable ama meeting that i’ve been a part of and there are a lot of people to thank for that. i had the honor of serving on the ama resident and fellow section governing council, leading the hod delegation with my partner-in-crime, delegate @markykash and the rest of our governing council consisting of chair colin murphy, immediate past chair @mlecuyer28, vice chair gunjan malhotra, board of trustees representative @ryanribeira, speaker eli freiman, vice speaker laura halpin, and member-at-large @hunterpattison. we were also able to welcome our chair-elect, the incomparable tani malhotra, our next candidate for the board of trustees @graysonwilkes.

in the house of delegates, we proudly supported policies to study patterns of physician suicide, identify models for systems addressing opioid mitigation, take a stronger stance on public health concerns related to vaping and e-cigarettes (just a day before the fda took a harder stance on the issue!), improve screening for domestic violence in lgbtq patients, recognize the full spectrum of gender identity and fluidity in response to recent moves by the trump administration, support the daca and dalca populations, increase support for post-marketing surveillance studies for drugs approved by fda-expedited review pathways, update and improve on principles and recommendations for addressing and mitigating student debt, continue to oppose unfunded mandates and their negative impact on patients and physicians, and improve ethical guidance on healthcare decision-making for parents and their children, to name just a few!

we also heard powerful testimony and were forced to take a hard look at internal policies on sexual and non-sexual harassment and recommended unanimously to bring in outside counsel to improve the processes and protect attendees and set an example on self-policing and combating harassment.

we also continued an ongoing discussion of gun violence as a major public health crisis, both as individuals (#thisisourlane) and as an organization. i’m excited to see what’s next and energized!
#amamtg #amarfs #membersmovemedicine @amermedicalassn #metoo #timesup

text:
continuamos com a canção do bandido  este sábado e domingo

últimas apresentações!

teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

classificação etária | m12

dias de espetáculo até 30 minutos após o início
segunda: encerrada

text:
en kortroman om tre kvinnor som ställer sig upp och kämpar, på gott och ont.
🌿
mia, sara och victoria har alla tre blivit nedtryckta av män på olika sätt. tillsammans beslutar de sig att ta tillbaka kontrollen över sina liv och kroppar. det blir början på en smärtsam kamp för frihet och hämnd.
🌿
det är härligt att läsa kortare berättelser emellanåt. jag önskar däremot att denna gick lite djupare i karaktärsbyggnad. jag vill veta hur och varför de beter sig som de gör ibland. vi får en övergripande bild över vilka dessa kvinnor är, men jag hade velat ha mer detaljer och trovärdighet. men jag tycker ändå att patriarkatet är läsvärd. sara har levt i ett destruktivt förhållande. mia går på en dejt med en man som våldtar och slår henne. victoria går sista året i gymnasiet (känns mer som sista året i högstadiet) och blir våldtagen av killen hon är förälskad i. det är lätt att känna med dessa kvinnor och man vill att de ska må bättre. mia som leder deras kamp går lite för långt, men det blir intressant. detta sker i andan av #metoo, utan att kvinnorna faktiskt använder metoorörelsen, de tar hellre kampen i sina egna händer. jag gillar att vi även får se från männens synvinkel, men de blir lätt lite stereotypiska. jag vet inte vad jag tycker om slutet. det gör att jag funderar på vad som egentligen är bokens budskap. någon som läst och har en tanke kring detta, utan att spoila för andra?
🌿
patriarkatet är en lättläst berättelse om tre utsatta kvinnor som vill ha makt över sina egna liv och kroppar, och vill lära männen en läxa som de sent kommer att glömma.
🌿
tack så mycket @ordberoendefrlag för recensionsexemplar!
🌿

text:
#thisisnotconsent: women are tweeting pictures of their underwear, and you should pay attention!

protesters wave underwear after ireland rape trial sparks fury. “you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front," said lawyer defending man later acquitted of raping teen.

on tuesday, lawmaker ruth coppinger held up a blue lacy thong in ireland's parliament, known as the dáil, to protest the government’s inaction over the issue of sexual consent. “it might seem embarrassing to show a pair of thongs here in this incongruous setting of the dáil,” she told fellow lawmakers. “but the reason i’m doing it is, how do you think a rape victim or a woman feels at the incongruous setting of her underwear being shown in court.” ⠀⠀⠀⠀
this is exactly why i do what i do. clothes do not define consent - say it over and over until you start believing it. victim blaming in court or anywhere else is wrong. if we can’t go to the police, if we can’t count on the justice system, who can we count on. join me my brothers and sisters. yes, #mentoo and post your sexy underwear or boxers/briefs in support of this victim and so many others who battle daily with coming forward because of results like this. post them with #thisisnotconsent ⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: yesterday while playing chess with our son, john says to me “have you noticed the strongest piece in chess is the queen- a woman? and the only one in the lot.” i actually had not! pretty badass, i thought, that back when chess was invented in the sixth century someone knew what was up. we travel all across the board in any direction we please unless we are blocked by the opposition (read: glass ceilings or patriarchy or racism). we can win the game too and most of the time we do but in collaboration. that’s the difference between the too-angry feminists who want to bring down the other side and the ones who simply want social justice for everyone: collaboration. we have all been waiting in the sidelines with our truths just below the surface... #metoo and #anythingyoucandoicandotoo and we’ve always known how strong we are. i see it in women’s faces, esp my momma friends and single momma friends who are juggling 50 things at a time, sometimes barely treading water, and always smiling and treating others with respect and unimaginable kindness-  despite everything. and we’ve all been patiently waiting for things to shift. i recognized that look of true confidence in maria callas’ face this morning as i was enjoying her talent... that unapologetic look of “excuse me while i sing you all under the table.” we’ve never been allowed too much strength or confidence. we’ve never even been allowed too much breakdown. but oh how the tables are turning!... 💪🏽 #justice #useyourpowertoempower #fiercenessisalwayswelcome #strength

text:
pre-holiday tip 1...
yesterday we discussed starting a dialogue with your child in preparation for all of the family time they may be experiencing over the next month. our first tip is to ask your child open-ended questions about the people who they may be encountering during these family events. for example, "how do you feel about going to see grandpa next week?", "what do you like about uncle jim and what don't you like about him?", or "what do you think about pastor smith or cousin sara?". give them the opportunity to answer the questions completely before asking additional clarifying questions and don't trivialize their opinions or try to convince them that they shouldn't feel the way they do. remember, how you as a parent experience a friend or family member can be very different than how a child experiences that individual, especially when sexual abuse is occurring/has occurred. it is critical that you listen attentively in these moments and gently probe when you hear responses that cause you concern or their body language, facial expressions or tone changes when a specific individual is being discussed. if you aren't sure if there is a need for concern based on your child's explanation about a specific family member or friend, take measures to keep your child isolated from this individual until you are sure.  #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
ich bin ein mann und nein ich trage diese wäsche nicht aber es muss ein zeichen gesetzt werden.

ein 27-jähriger mann in irland soll eine 17-jährige vergewaltigt haben. er wurde freigesprochen. seine anwältin sagte über das vermeintliche opfer: „sie müssen sich ansehen, wie sie angezogen war. sie hat einen string-tanga mit spitze getragen.“ das sei beweis genug gewesen, dass die junge frau mit ihm sex haben wollte. 🤯🤯🤯 das hat eine irische abgeordnete derart aufgeregt, dass sie mit ihrer unterwäsche während der parlamentsdebatte wedelte. sie forderte, dass das parlament dringend gegen beschuldigungen von opfern vorgehen müsse.
viele junge frauen posten deshalb unter #thisisnotconsent ihre unterwäsche, um so ein zeichen zu setzen, gegen #victimblaming und für solidarität mit opfern sexualisierter gewalt. ich habe mir erlaubt, mich da anzuschließen. ich wünsche mir, dass die leute zuhören, reflektiert nachdenken und endlich das verstehen, was wirklich gemeint ist. .
.
.
.
.

text:
okay i was aaaaaaabout the first snow fall yesterday here in philly, but when i ventured out a few hours later to go to happy hour? not so much 🤣
〰️
i really do love the snow. something about it is still so magical to me, like i’m a kid again and waiting on the news to call my school’s name for a day off. with that being said, i slip every.freaking.year walking to work 🤣😩 so i’m just anticipating this year’s snowy slip lol.
〰️
on a more serious note, i read a lot about the story of a rape victim in ireland this morning, whose rapist was acquitted, and the woman’s underwear being brought in as evidence. “you have to look at the way she was dressed,” they said. “she was wearing a thong.” coincidentally, in the photo above, i’m wearing a dress that i posted about a few weeks ago - when a stranger passing me on my commute to work told me to pull my skirt down. here’s your daily reminder that what you wear has nothing to do with consent of any kind. your thong doesn’t mean you were asking to be raped, and your skirt doesn’t mean you asked for anyone’s opinion. #thisisnotconsent
.
.
.

"il mio tanga non significa che dico sì". la protesta delle donne sui social arriva anche in italia

text:
varför gör jag detta? 
jag skrev inte min bok för att jag vill hålla mig kvar i mitt förflutna att jag inte kan gå vidare och lämna allt bakom mig! 
jag skrev boken för att skapa förändringar , göra skillnad vara med och påverka att detta är inte ok!!!! 😡
jag delar min historia för att öppna upp för diskussioner, att hjälpa andra för jag vet att jag är långt ifrån ensam. :( mitt helvete började väldigt tidigt men fortfarande 2018 har vi  bara kommit en liten bit fortfarande är det långt kvar det skulle behövas ett krafttag från beslutsfattarna!! när jag lämnade så fanns ingen hjälp från samhället att få!!! tack!! för att kriscentrum fanns där🙏 och mina vänner ❤️ hade aldrig orkat dra detta tunga lass om det inte var för dem 🙏❤️ men ska det vara så?? nej! 
jag älskar livet ❤️ med allt vad det innebär för första gången kan jag se längre än dag för dag. mina kommande planer och min framtid ☀️
så tack alla ni som delar min historia och vill läsa min bok ❤️❤️❤️
haft lite mycket på sistone men efter helgen kommer jag att uppdatera på instagram och min boksida på fb med klipp, och foton så följ mig gärna. 
ta hand om er !! massa kramar ❤️#våldinärarelationer#psykiskohälsa#våld#frånknytnävsslagtillegenidentitet#författare#debut#metoo#ingen#kan#tysta#mig #tahandomer#tillsammans#är#vi#starka#❤️❤️❤️

text:
read caption-
does it ever feel like all this is just too much to handle?
like you sitting in your home, with your family. 
your dad is sipping his evening tea while your mother is watching her favourite show and they are even conversing in between. 
everything is fine. 
it's okay.
because that is what "fine" is supposed to be like, right?
and suddenly, you are not able to breathe. 
it's as if this "fine" environment is suffocating you.
you think that maybe it's because of the noise and you'll feel better if you just go outside and walk in the balcony. 
but even when you are walking, you are still not able to breathe. and you start thinking that maybe it's the silence. 
it's like the air is going in through your mouth but it's not reaching to your lungs, your body or most importantly, to your soul. you think that you're going to die, this is the end. suddenly somebody taps on your shoulder, you look back, it's your parents with concerned look on their faces. and in that exact moment, the air from this entire universe gathers and satisfies your soul. 
but, as the moment passes by you, are you thankful? 
do you think that, thank god that you have some people in your life who'll never leave you, no matter what happens? 
do you feel thankful towards the universe for giving you this one more precious chance to breathe peacefully? 
or do you go on, cursing this blissful life that you are given? 
claiming that how your life sucks while there are thousands of people out there who'll maybe even die, just to live a day of this blessed life of yours? 
what is it?

text:
where my people pleasers?

#metoo

can i share something i learned? 
when we are trying to please other people, we are trying to get love.  whoa- how shockingly true is that?? that statement hit me right in the face- most of my life that’s how i felt accepted. 
let me tell you- there are times when i still “worry” or over think what other people may or may not think about me or my business or my kids or what whatever- but like 98% of the time idgaf- this is my life and i get one to really live!

y’all we gotta stop giving away pieces of ourselves just to make other happy or comfortable!

listen, you can not ever pay enough to get someone else’s love.

you are worthy and enough just as you are- even if that means you don’t fit inside someone else’s box!

text:
secretary devos just proposed a rule that would make schools less safe for survivors of sexual assault and harassment, when there is already alarmingly high rates of campus sexual assaults and harassment that go unreported.

it promotes a process that inappropriately favors the accused and would let schools ignore their responsibility under title ix to respond promptly and fairly to complaints of sexual violence.

we will continue to support survivors.

text: 为什么别人有的自由，我们不能拥有。明明是同一个国家出生，为什么他们就要被re education，我们拥抱爱情，拥抱友情，我们有权谈性说爱，有权决定生与不生，有权享受作为一个独立个体的存在。可这里没有人尊重自由。要我爱这里的什么呢。#metoo 我做瓷国人做的好痛苦啊。

rape in greek mythology⠀
the rape of women was a common theme throughout greek mythology. the god zeus himself was part of many rape stories – in which he ‘sexually violated’ antiope, europa and leda the nymph, among others.  medusa was raped by poseidon and was subsequently also punished for being raped in athena’s temple, and turned into a monster.⠀
⠀
read further on the history of rape culture and how women have always been suspect of some degree of acquiescence, and how rape trials have focused on the victims having to prove their innocence and lack of consent, more than determining the accountability of perpetrators in the blog: “actresses in the history of rape culture”: https://buff.ly/2dkmdou⠀
⠀

text:
"i wouldn't have been able to verbalise what had happened to me because anyway i didn't know what had happened to me." you did this to yourself, 2011.

many of the images from my piece are accompanied by text. i collected these pieces of text from courtroom transcripts, news reports and interviews in liz kelly's 'surviving sexual violence' (1988). back in 2011 these seemed the best sources of speech about sexual violence. nowadays i suppose i could use the huge mass of descriptive statements on hashtags like #metoo. there is much more out there than in 2011, but somehow not much has changed. there is an amnesia about sexual violence - survivor stories have been transcribed again and again each decade, but somehow we still think these stories are new. we still think their revelation will issue change. the more i research this topic, the more i think that survivor stories are not the avenue to lasting legal and political change that will protect survivors and would-be survivors. 
#sexualviolence #survivors #wordsandpictures

text: #gratitude day 4. today because i feel more miserable with a cold on top of incredible stress of this week. i’m going to say something i almost never say. i am grateful i am still here. i’ve gone back and forth about sharing this on social media because there’s many backstabbers who use posts against people. but in light of the #metoo movement i’ve decided to share. i’ve struggled with major depression most of my life. i’ve been suicidal many, many times but yet i continue to be here, mostly because i don’t want to rush into something that’s coming for all of us any way. i also have chronic pain conditions. i know i have many fellow #spoonies who understand. every day when i get out of bed (i’d love to say wake up but i rarely sleep) i want to give up. i want to die because of the horrible pain that i am in. but instead i get up, go to work and try to lead as normal a life as i can. i’ve tried many things, therapy, medications, multiple medications, exercise, trying to eat better, attempting a social life, herbal supplements, meditation, etc. you name it, i’ve probably tried.i try not to complain too much because people do not care. people are selfish and only care about themselves, we’re in a “me first and only” type of culture. but this is all because i want to share a specific part of what has helped me. if you are suicidal, odds are you don’t want to die, but some part of your life does need to die. if you are low look at your life, what in it needs to die? what do you need to stop giving energy to? family? friends? need a new job? try to identify it if you possibly can (which i know is a monumental task  when you have depression) and do it. stop giving it energy, cut it out, get rid of it, kill it, change it. give yourself back that energy to use in literally anything that brings you even the slightest glimmer of hope. and if you think that no one in the world cares, i assure you that someone, somewhere in some aspect cares about you. even if it’s the person you held the door open for at dunkin and gave you a genuine smile. i care about you. i get it. and i see you, and i love you. thank you for staying in this world with me. i am grateful for you too.

text:
w związku z ostatnimi wydarzeniami w irlandii, uniewinnieniem gwalciciela 17-letniej dziewczynki oraz protestami kobiet zaangażowanych w te sprawe, dzisiaj post w tym temacie ⚠️ nie każdy zna sytuację, więc streszcze po krotce : mężczyzna został uniewinniony, ponieważ ofiara miała na sobie koronkowa bieliznę, co obrońca przedstawił jako dowód na chęć dziewczyny do współżycia. cała obrona opierała się na #victimblaming. ławie przysięgłych, w której znajdowały się 4 kobiety i 8 mężczyzn, to wystarczyło. więcej szczegółów można znaleźć na stronie independent: https://ind.pn/2qxclcp

niestety nie tylko w irlandii prawo kuleje w takich sytuacjach. dlatego polecam wam reportaż "polska odwraca oczy" autorstwa @justyna.kopinska . warto wiedzieć co się dzieje u nas w kraju. jak działa kodeks karny, jak okrutnym przestępcom udaje się uniknąć odpowiedzialności, jak ofiary gwałtów i przemocy muszą sobie radzić ze świadomością że ich oprawcy chodzą po ulicach. 
mnie chyba najbardziej poruszył reportaż, w którym autorka opisała co działo się na oddziale dziecięcym szpitala dla psychicznie chorych w starogardzie gdańskim, moim rodzinnym mieście. jak toturowano dzieci, które same nie umiały się bronić. przy czym osoba odpowiedzialna za te okropnosci unikała wyroku przez lata, pracując jako biegła sądu okręgowego w gdańsku... raz na jakiś czas w internecie wypływają na wierzch takie historie. niestety, mam wrażenie że niektórzy ludzie nie traktują ich poważnie, bo uważają że akcje typu #metoo lub #thisisnotconsent nic nie dają poszkodowanym😔 moim zdaniem nie mają racji. warto jest o tym mówić, bo prawo wciąż nie jest doskonałe i nie pociąga do odpowiedzialności w wielu okrutnych sprawach.

text:
hari ini 16 november adalah hari toleransi sedunia. saya & teman teman meluncurkan festival film ber nama 16filmfest yang mendukung toleransi atas segala perbedaan di muka bumi ini. perbedaan etnis, budaya, agama, semua seharusnya bisa memperkaya hidup kita dan memperkuat persaudaraan sesama.
namun, perbedaan kadang melegitimasi terjadinya kekerasan. padahal manusia bernurani dan kemanusiaan seharusnya tidak mentolerir segala bentuk kekerasan. bahasa kerennya zero tolerance, bahasa indonesianya nol toleransi. lewat pemutaran film, @enam belasffest mengkampanyekan nol toleransi atas kekerasan berbasis gender dan seksual.
festival film yang akan ber langsung selama 16 hari ini, dari mulai 25 november sampai 10 desember, akan memutar 16 film panjang dan 16 film pendek yang pastinya bisa meningkatkan awareness kita atas segala bentuk kekerasan sambil mencari solusi bersama untuk mengakhirinya. terimakasih @komnas_perempuan @unaids.id @aliansi1visi @viu indonesia@nadianasoetion & semua teman2 filmmakers yang sudah berpartisipadi meminjamkan filmnya, juga semua volunteers & ambassadors tersayang  #toleranceday #internationaltoleranceday #16daysofactivism #16haktp #zerotolerance #genderbasedviolence #hearmetoo #metoo #movement #indonesia #filmfestival #communityfirst #empoweringwomen #allequal #lgbtiq #rainbowwarriors #enambelasffest

text:
🖤❤️i am...❤️🖤
i’ve been working on this piece for a few months now. it’s mixed medium. it’s titled i am your sister, your mother, your cousin, your aunt, your next door neighbor...or just i am... for short. it is dedicated to all the women, all over the world, that have experienced sexual assault and/or rape, or anyone woman who has a story they are too afraid to tell. women are the backbone of our society, we need to build each other up. i know that if we can come together, nothing can stop us from changing the world. #art #streetart #mixedmedium #lgbtq #metoo #metoomovement #womensrights #gay #lesbian #womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #womeninspiringwomen #womensart #artist #artistsoninstagram #arty #artwork #artstagram

text:
tänkte prata lite om det här med representation, och då framförallt brist på representation.
i hela metoo upproret var det väldigt få icke-vita som fick sina röster hörda, vi alla vet att hela upproret och metoo startades av en svart kvinna men fick helt ny nivå av uppmärksamhet när en vit kvinna började prata om det.
(jag syftar då på att den vita kvinnan fick mer plats pga sin hudfärg)
vi vet också att vita oftast blir närmast förolämpade när man påpekar att woc röster inte hörs på samma sätt, och de vita feministernas svar är oftast "kampen är större än så" eller "men ni exkluderar ju själva vita kvinnors röster så ni är inte bättre själva" när vi admin har försökt prata om vårt konto och vårt syfte. en påstod att vi förolämpade tarana burke när vi valde att höja woc röster eftersom tarana är svart, jag försöker för övrigt fortfarande förstå den logiken.
men, när vita feminister svarar på detta sätt, upplevs det som att de faktiskt som att vita feminister inte riktigt tycker att vi förtjänar en plats i deras rum, och att de bara bryr sig om kampen som gäller dem och gärna använder woc för att sedan kasta oss under bussen för deras eget gynnande.
nedan kommer en länk på en artikel som jag upplevde väldigt intressant och fler woc åsikter och upplevelser delades:
https://m.huffpost.com/us/entry/us_5a442d73e4b0b0e5a7a4992c?guccounter=1

text:
a story that i've been horrified reading about this week is that of the court case of the alleged rapist of a 17 year old girl in #ireland the 27 year old man's defence lawyer basically said that how this girl was dressed was a problem and that she was effectively up for it. what she was referring to was the #lace front #thong that the victim was wearing. the fact that this sentiment came from a woman has absolutely blown my mind 😬
.
.
the man was found not guilty. now whether he is or not, i don't know, but what i do know is that the underwear any woman chooses to wear on any given day does not relate to her willingness to have sex with someone. it got me to thinking that nearly all of my female clients wear thongs when they see me, and many of my male clients go completely naked purely as it makes it easier for me to work the glutes without material getting in the way. this lawyer would presumably think that the sexual abuse of any of these people would be justified as they chose to get naked or wear a thong 🤔 yeah seriously, how frightening?! .
.
now my lawyer husband made the point that as the defence lawyer, she'll say anything to try and get her client off as that's her job. i get that, but surely at some point in cases like this, this level of opinion cannot be applied. i'm amazed the judge didn't ask for the statement to be retracted. i'm sure this woman doesn't believe this girl deserved it, but what are we teaching young men and boys when that is put forward as a reasonable excuse to rape someone. the mind boggles!
.
so women in support of this young lady are posting pics of their thongs with the hashtag #thisisnotconsent so here is one of mine, just casually left in my hallway! it's simple folks.... #nomeansno #ibelieveher
.

text_retweet:
i’m so proud to announce that i’ll be speaking at the @lolaretreat in la in feb. this retreat is a bold money event for bold women. why is a #nondietdietitian speaking at a #womensfinance conference?  because as women, we are the main targets of #dietculture and it’s time we all understand the psychology and marketing that the #diet and #wellness industries use to convince you to keep spending your time, energy and money. this session will help you understand some of the reasons why we keep being seduced by these industries that claim to have your health as a priority when it’s really about boosting their bottom line. register with the code melissa and get a $50 off on your registration. #repost @lolaretreat with @get_repost
・・・
new session alert! whether you're on a diet, no diet or hate diets, diet culture impacts us all. and it's costing us a pretty penny financially, mentally and emotionally. which is why i'm thrilled to have @mburton0214 teach this workshop at lola la.
---- how the diet and wellness industry is making you broke on every level

the health and wellness industry has been pioneered and dominated by women. women are also primarily responsible for making the health and wellness industry a multi trillion dollar industry. our current culture dictates that not only should women be and do it all, they should look (and feel!) flawlessly amazing while accomplishing their goals and living their best lives (insert eye roll here). even in the empowered #metoo era, women are still being convinced that they need to invest their money and energy in the dreams promised by the diet and wellness industry in order to even deserve a healthy, happy and successful life (yes, i’m looking at you, goop). in this session you’ll learn how and why the diet and wellness industry is seducing you - as a smart and motivated woman - to place your hard earned dollars and precious headspace into their hands. in this session melissa burton, a former marketing manager and current registered dietitian nutritionist (and registered yoga teacher), will help you understand the depth, breath and power of diet culture and how to lessen its impact on your wallet, mind, heart and soul
name: Melissa Burton, RDN, RYT-200

text:
last week in ireland a man got away with rape just because of the type of thong the girl was wearing... a series of protests over sexual consent have been taking place, after a man was acquitted of raping a 17-year-old girl.

in the trail, the (female) defence lawyer told the jury: "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front." the man was found "not guilty"!! on tuesday, lawmaker ruth coppinger held up a lacy thong in ireland's parliament, to protest the goverment's inaction over the issue of sexual consent. 
#thisisnotconsent #sexualassault #sexualabuse #metoo #rapistcauserape #ruthcoppinger #istandwiththewomanofireland #stopvictimblaming #victimblaming #herbodyherchoice #herchoice #womansrights##nomeansno #timesup #feminism #cork #dublin #ireland

text:
[一級方程式]

賽車女郎絕跡 formula 1

雖然近年多了女性觀眾和車手參予，不過賽車運動一向是男士們喜愛和主導的項目，長久以來賽車場地都會有不少穿著漂亮的賽車女郎，在開賽前負責舉起倒數的時間牌，提醒車手和工作人員，這亦是男性觀眾期待的環節。不過日前 f1 賽會宣佈一個可能令不少觀眾失望的決定。

2018 新賽季會在 3 月 25 日在澳州墨爾本拉開戰幔，屆時觀眾將不會再見到漂亮的賽車女郎在賽道出現。近年女權主義日益抬頭，賽車女郎被他們認為是對女性的歧視，今次 f1 賽會的決定就是避免賽車女郎成為爭議焦點。不過並非所有車迷都認同，有人認為賽會向一班太得閒的女權主義者跪低，而其他賽事亦未有仿效，美國的 nascar 早前跟贊助商 monster energy 簽約，他們高調宣佈會引進 monster energy 女郎為賽事增添氣氛。

source：cnbeta 
#feminism #metoo #justice #world #awareness
name: 評權男女 Gender Equality Please

text:
[環保 vs 女權]

女權:為環保唔用飲管「直接飲」，係打壓女性

我們想讓你知道的是
近來與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多。有一種聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視。

環保署禁塑膠吸管政策公布之後，與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多，從安全、衛生到製造過程的汙染等，都產生了非常多的熱烈討論。有一種質疑聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視，隱含了男性特權／陽剛霸權在內。

一、吸管使用的性別化
在父權社會中，對不同性別有著不同的期待。男生要陽剛、女生要陰柔，而在「吃相」這件事情上，也存在性別化的規訓。

女性長期被期待吃東西要「秀氣」，許多家長、同儕與外人們，都要求女性吃喝東西要安靜、闔嘴、小口、細嚼慢嚥等，這形成一種有形無形的社會壓力，也塑造了女性的生活飲食習慣。也因此，由於喝飲料使用吸管，正符合對女性的期待，所以在我的成長經驗中，女孩子使用吸管的次數是多於男孩子的，因為這樣看起來比較「淑女」。 二、避免唇膏掉色的需求
畢竟我們身處父權資本主義社會，在職場歧視、消費文化與性別期待的交織影響下，女性比男性更被要求要化妝，甚至有些場合視作是基本禮儀與明文規定。那就不得不講到，唇膏與吸管使用的密切關聯。

包含我在內的許多女性，化妝吃東西最怕的就是「唇膏掉色」，我們也很想盡情享受美食，卻又擔心等回要去洗手間補妝，老實說很是麻煩。所以這時候，吸管的使用就可以減少這層焦慮。辦公室裡一杯手搖飲料補充糖分，又不需要來來回回跑洗手間補妝，也可以避免被上司以「妝容」或「常不在座位」刁難。

三、懷孕臥床的經驗
除了少部分跨性別與間性人族群，大部分會懷孕生育的是女性，然而在待產到分娩完的時候，經常必須要長時間臥床，很多事情並不像平常時方便。我身邊許多有懷孕生育經驗的女性親友告訴我，在這段期間內連吃喝東西都成了問題，很怕東西會灑滿整個床榻，這時候吸管就扮演了非常重要的角色。

試著想想，平常再怎麼大剌剌的女性，在臥床期間也不能像過往一樣，即使平常沒有使用吸管的習慣，也可能會為了能方便飲食而使用。

結語
或許講到這裡，會有人反駁我說，這些女性生命經驗都是父權枷鎖，所以我們應該拋棄它，鼓勵女性「直接喝」才對。但女性主義並非對女性的另一種規訓，女性還是可以選擇用自己習慣的方式生活。

而且也不是所有女性都有足夠安全平等的環境，讓她們選擇不受拘束，這是目前的物質現實，所以女性主義更強調女性的選擇權，以及對女性處境的分析，讓女性經驗及需求能被平等地重視善待。所以總結來說，環保吸管對於許多女性而言，也是一種不可或缺的發明，它給了女性更友善環境，可以同時關心自身需求與地球的方式，也因此環保吸管是女性主義的另類象徵。

source: the news lens關鍵評論網

#feminism #metoo #gender #equality #peace #social #world #awareness

或許講到這裡，會有人反駁我說，這些女性生命經驗都是父權枷鎖，所以我們應該拋棄它，鼓勵女性「直接喝」才對。但女性主義並非對女性的另一種規訓，女性還是可以選擇用自己習慣的方式生活。

而且也不是所有女性都有足夠安全平等的環境，讓她們選擇不受拘束，這是目前的物質現實，所以女性主義更強調女性的選擇權，以及對女性處境的分析，讓女性經驗及需求能被平等地重視善待。所以總結來說，環保吸管對於許多女性而言，也是一種不可或缺的發明，它給了女性更友善環境，可以同時關心自身需求與地球的方式，也因此環保吸管是女性主義的另類象徵。

stop_filter_tweet: [ 環保 vs 女權 ] 女權 : 為環保唔用飲管「直接飲」，係打壓女性 我們想讓你知道的是 近來與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多。有一種聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視。 環保署禁塑膠吸管政策公布之後，與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多，從安全、衛生到製造過程的汙染等，都產生了非常多的熱烈討論。有一種質疑聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視，隱含了男性特權／陽剛霸權在內。 一、吸管使用的性別化 在父權社會中，對不同性別有著不同的期待。男生要陽剛、女生要陰柔，而在「吃相」這件事情上，也存在性別化的規訓。 女性長期被期待吃東西要「秀氣」，許多家長、同儕與外人們，都要求女性吃喝東西要安靜、闔嘴、小口、細嚼慢嚥等，這形成一種有形無形的社會壓力，也塑造了女性的生活飲食習慣。也因此，由於喝飲料使用吸管，正符合對女性的期待，所以在我的成長經驗中，女孩子使用吸管的次數是多於男孩子的，因為這樣看起來比較「淑女」。 二、避免唇膏掉色的需求 畢竟我們身處父權資本主義社會，在職場歧視、消費文化與性別期待的交織影響下，女性比男性更被要求要化妝，甚至有些場合視作是基本禮儀與明文規定。那就不得不講到，唇膏與吸管使用的密切關聯。 包含我在內的許多女性，化妝吃東西最怕的就是「唇膏掉色」，我們也很想盡情享受美食，卻又擔心等回要去洗手間補妝，老實說很是麻煩。所以這時候，吸管的使用就可以減少這層焦慮。辦公室裡一杯手搖飲料補充糖分，又不需要來來回回跑洗手間補妝，也可以避免被上司以「妝容」或「常不在座位」刁難。 三、懷孕臥床的經驗 除了少部分跨性別與間性人族群，大部分會懷孕生育的是女性，然而在待產到分娩完的時候，經常必須要長時間臥床，很多事情並不像平常時方便。我身邊許多有懷孕生育經驗的女性親友告訴我，在這段期間內連吃喝東西都成了問題，很怕東西會灑滿整個床榻，這時候吸管就扮演了非常重要的角色。 試著想想，平常再怎麼大剌剌的女性，在臥床期間也不能像過往一樣，即使平常沒有使用吸管的習慣，也可能會為了能方便飲食而使用。 結語 或許講到這裡，會有人反駁我說，這些女性生命經驗都是父權枷鎖，所以我們應該拋棄它，鼓勵女性「直接喝」才對。但女性主義並非對女性的另一種規訓，女性還是可以選擇用自己習慣的方式生活。 而且也不是所有女性都有足夠安全平等的環境，讓她們選擇不受拘束，這是目前的物質現實，所以女性主義更強調女性的選擇權，以及對女性處境的分析，讓女性經驗及需求能被平等地重視善待。所以總結來說，環保吸管對於許多女性而言，也是一種不可或缺的發明，它給了女性更友善環境，可以同時關心自身需求與地球的方式，也因此環保吸管是女性主義的另類象徵。 source : news lens關鍵評論網

stem_filter: [ 環保 vs 女權 ] 女權 : 為環保唔用飲管「直接飲」，係打壓女性 我們想讓你知道的是 近來與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多。有一種聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視。 環保署禁塑膠吸管政策公布之後，與「環保吸管」相關的質疑與爭議越來越多，從安全、衛生到製造過程的汙染等，都產生了非常多的熱烈討論。有一種質疑聲浪是，環保吸管的製造過程一樣會消耗能源、汙染環境，那不如「直接喝」就好了，這樣似乎是最環保的方式。但筆者作為女性的生命經驗告訴我，這種說法是對女性生命經驗的忽視，隱含了男性特權／陽剛霸權在內。 一、吸管使用的性別化 在父權社會中，對不同性別有著不同的期待。男生要陽剛、女生要陰柔，而在「吃相」這件事情上，也存在性別化的規訓。 女性長期被期待吃東西要「秀氣」，許多家長、同儕與外人們，都要求女性吃喝東西要安靜、闔嘴、小口、細嚼慢嚥等，這形成一種有形無形的社會壓力，也塑造了女性的生活飲食習慣。也因此，由於喝飲料使用吸管，正符合對女性的期待，所以在我的成長經驗中，女孩子使用吸管的次數是多於男孩子的，因為這樣看起來比較「淑女」。 二、避免唇膏掉色的需求 畢竟我們身處父權資本主義社會，在職場歧視、消費文化與性別期待的交織影響下，女性比男性更被要求要化妝，甚至有些場合視作是基本禮儀與明文規定。那就不得不講到，唇膏與吸管使用的密切關聯。 包含我在內的許多女性，化妝吃東西最怕的就是「唇膏掉色」，我們也很想盡情享受美食，卻又擔心等回要去洗手間補妝，老實說很是麻煩。所以這時候，吸管的使用就可以減少這層焦慮。辦公室裡一杯手搖飲料補充糖分，又不需要來來回回跑洗手間補妝，也可以避免被上司以「妝容」或「常不在座位」刁難。 三、懷孕臥床的經驗 除了少部分跨性別與間性人族群，大部分會懷孕生育的是女性，然而在待產到分娩完的時候，經常必須要長時間臥床，很多事情並不像平常時方便。我身邊許多有懷孕生育經驗的女性親友告訴我，在這段期間內連吃喝東西都成了問題，很怕東西會灑滿整個床榻，這時候吸管就扮演了非常重要的角色。 試著想想，平常再怎麼大剌剌的女性，在臥床期間也不能像過往一樣，即使平常沒有使用吸管的習慣，也可能會為了能方便飲食而使用。 結語 或許講到這裡，會有人反駁我說，這些女性生命經驗都是父權枷鎖，所以我們應該拋棄它，鼓勵女性「直接喝」才對。但女性主義並非對女性的另一種規訓，女性還是可以選擇用自己習慣的方式生活。 而且也不是所有女性都有足夠安全平等的環境，讓她們選擇不受拘束，這是目前的物質現實，所以女性主義更強調女性的選擇權，以及對女性處境的分析，讓女性經驗及需求能被平等地重視善待。所以總結來說，環保吸管對於許多女性而言，也是一種不可或缺的發明，它給了女性更友善環境，可以同時關心自身需求與地球的方式，也因此環保吸管是女性主義的另類象徵。 sourc : news lens關鍵評論網

text:
why are we the most "connected" generation of all time, yet are in reality the most disconnected?

check out the link in bio for a short documentary called brain, heart, world. or view on the @fightthenewdrug profile.

one of the biggest problems is being connected physically, socially, or (or electronically), but disconnected in heart and soul.

porn is one of the biggest soul killers in our society? why? well one reason is its deceptiveness. it is sold as a connector, as an enhancer, and as "freedom" or liberty in sexuality.

in reality, it is bondage. not the "sexy" kind of bondage. the actual enslavement bondage. it is the disconnection of your brain, heart, and soul. it is the slow breakdown and separation of body, soul, and spirit.

think it doesnt affect you? i'd challenge you to learn some of the facts, and then think again.

this is a massive detriment to society. are you disgusted by men like harvey weinstein, who have sexually abused countless women? that mentality is driven and fueled by porn. it is allowed to to exist and grow. it is heralded. porn consumption ultimately drives human trafficking. 
as the statue of liberty is a symbol of freedom to the worn and weary who come to our country looking for a fresh beginning, i pray some of this scientific material will help bring freedom to the life of someone you know.

i don't share this to bring shame or condemnation on people. i share to bring light and awareness. this stuff isn't easy to talk about, just like it isn't easy for me to encourage someone who is really unhealthy and overweight to stop eating sugar. but i love that person enough to step in and help bring awareness to the damage being done, and show steps towards health and freedom. 
if you want to do the same, then share this message.

#freedomfriday #brainheartworld #nopornnovember #metoo  #humantrafficking #makeachange
#truefreedom #statueofliberty

text:
“at the end of the day, we can endure much more than we think we can.” ~frida kahlo🌹

the 12th annual walk against rape 🚺 april 8, 2017 
this walk aims to: •raise awareness in san francisco around issues with sexual violence. provide a space for survivors of sexual violence to heal and celebrate their survival. •educate the community about resources available in the aftermath of assault.
•raise money for san francisco’s only community based rape crisis center. create community and shared experiences of sexual violence so as to not isolate further the experience.
•to make visible what has historically been silenced and invisible. 
for more info: http://sfwar.org/walk/

text:
#nakedwerise day 6 #photochallenge 
f r e e d o m

this year's challenge happens to end synchronoistically with venus coming out of the underworld. 
what perfect timing. in human design, the gate venus has been gate 44 since early october, per astrologer kim gould.

this is the gate of welcoming the royal bride. the bride is coming, she is pregnant with the heir to the throne. the castle and surrounding lands must be prepared for her.
how are you preparing for the pregnant bride who is approaching your gate right now? how are you making room for such a powerful feminine presence to enter? how are you preparing yourself as her arrival changes everything forevermore?

what parts of you are you/your life are you are dying off and what are you cultivating and creating? what qualities will be taking your throne?

are you still free to love and relationship to your wounds?
are you ready to receive your equal within you and what does that look like?

robots can create, but there is always an underlying pattern, some sort of program.  we are moving beyond the program, beyond the scripted, the controlled, the absolute and into a new world of creation.  we are doing that by becoming conscious of what we value, what we love, what makes us happy and feel well.

how can we acknowledge what a fountain of wisdom we are and are becoming?

one last inspiration: “everything i’ve ever done, everything i’ve ever learned,” she says, “i’m using all of that stuff right now. and all the women that reside in me are now operative.” ~betty reid soskin, 97 year old female park ranger ⚓
☆
i salute you, bow and cheer you on as you continue to live with heart courage! aloha!
☆ 🌈 -- always best aloha,

veruschka 💃
☆

this year's challenge happens to end synchronoistically with venus coming out of the underworld. 
what perfect timing. in human design, the gate venus has been gate 44 since early october, per astrologer kim gould.

this is the gate of welcoming the royal bride. the bride is coming, she is pregt with the heir to the throne. the castle and surrounding lands must be prepared for her.
how are you preparing for the pregt bride who is approaching your gate right now? how are you making room for such a powerful feminine presence to enter? how are you preparing yourself as her arrival changes everything forevermore?

what parts of you are you/your life are you are dying off and what are you cultivating and creating? what qualities will be taking your throne?

are you still free to love and relationship to your wounds?
are you ready to receive your equal within you and what does that look like?

robots can create, but there is always an underlying pattern, some sort of program.  we are moving beyond the program, beyond the scripted, the controlled, the absolute and into a new world of creation.  we are doing that by becoming conscious of what we value, what we love, what makes us happy and feel well.

how can we acknowledge what a fountain of wisdom we are and are becoming?

one last inspiration: “everything i’ve ever done, everything i’ve ever learned,” she says, “i’m using all of that stuff right now. and all the women that reside in me are now operative.” ~betty reid soskin, 97 year old female park ranger ⚓
☆
i salute you, bow and cheer you on as you continue to live with heart courage! aloha!
☆ 🌈 -- always best aloha,

veruschka 💃

text:
a cork, in irlanda, un uomo di 27 anni è stato assolto dalla accusa di violenza sessuale solo perché la ragazzina (17 anni) indossava un perizoma. 
una sentenza assurda e ingiustificabile. un capo di vestiario, così come un atteggiamento, non è – e non potrà essere mai – consenso. 
e’ successo in irlanda, vero, ma è indicativo di come i diritti e le conquiste fatte negli anni non si debbano mai dare per scontate, ma difendere quotidianamente in ogni angolo del mondo. anche e soprattutto in quella parte che con supponenza riteniamo civilizzata e culturalmente avanzata. 
donna colpevole sempre e comunque, donna vittima due volte. che se la cerca, insomma. come troppe volte siamo costretti ad ascoltare anche qui da noi.
e’ una vergogna. ed è inaccettabile. 
#thisisnotconsent è lo slogan che sta riempendo le piazze reali e virtuali d’irlanda, lanciato dal gruppo “donne d’irlanda”. ripetiamolo forte, tutti insieme. questo non è consenso. *
*
*
*
*

text:
illustrazione per il manifesto del festival la violenza illustrata della casa delle donne di bologna, dal 7 novembre al 4 dicembre a bologna.

il titolo di questa edizione è "taci, anzi parla". un titolo importante che cita carla lonzi per parlare del dibattito che ha avuto grande spazio nell’informazione mainstream e non solo: la narrazione, il racconto in prima persona, l’uscita collettiva delle donne che hanno subito violenza a partire dal mondo del cinema e dello spettacolo fino agli spazi del lavoro e della quotidianità di ognuna. #illustration #ritapetruccioli #festivallaviolenzaillustrata #casadelledonne #tacianziparla #nonunadimeno #metoo #feminism #bologna
name: Rita Petruccioli
tweet_full:

text:
never alone

as often as these words have been expressed especially with the #metoo movement, i hope every single person reading this understands the power of simply reaching out.

i can't tell you how many times i needed to simply vent, needed to know someone – anyone – simply cared.

it breaks my heart to know we're so afraid of showing our weakness.

we're afraid of being judged.
we're afraid we'll look foolish.
but it's not worth it. our ego is not worth us staying in our lowest of lows.
it's not worth you having to deal with a broken heart on your own.

it's not worth you questioning your worth to your family, friends, to the world. 
it's not worth you feeling trapped with whatever deep dark secret you think will make you unlovable.

even if it's simply me – a random stranger on instagram – please send a message. do not wait until you're on your last string of sanity.

we all do a great job of sharing the 'pretty' mask to which everyone seems to enjoy. 
we tend to hold it all together. always smiling in pictures. looking flawless, on point, whatever.

that's. not. real.
it's not human.
we hurt. we hold on to pain. disappointment tear us apart.

if there's every anything i can ever do to listen, to help ease pain, or even just to reassure you you're not alone – please give me that honor of serving you. please help me.
i need you to know you're loved, admired, worthy, & adored. 
you are never alone ♥

text:
femme wave presents: sex hysteria afterimage [part 1/10]: an instagram exhibition by @prdct
.
. 
in the age of #metoo, sexual violence is front and center on everyone’s feeds. since the movement’s virality began in late 2017, hundreds of people throughout the twitterverse have opened up to the internet with their experiences of sexual harassment and violence in the workplace. though #solidarity and strength through this sharing of experiences is overwhelmingly evident, one cannot help but notice willful ignorance in the midst of it all: a community left out of a conversation whose members should, in fact, be at the forefront of. .
.
#wherearethesexworkers? .
.
in conversations of #autonomy, #consent, and #violence against marginalized peoples, there is something to be said about the importance of the role of the sex worker. they have unique qualifications to speak on these topics, given their jobs and the astronomical levels of abuse and violence they face (they experience a higher rate of sexual harassment and assault than any other group of people), but are rarely invited to the conversation. more often than not, people working in the sex industry are pushed *out* of #metoo and other discussions on similar topics due to poor representation and stigmatism surrounding the identities of sex workers and how they make their money… a consequence of hysteria created by the government and the media which has resulted in rampant #whorephobia, often topped with nuances of racism and sexism to boot. .
.
whorephobia: “the hatred of, oppression of, violence towards, and discrimination against sex workers; and by extension derision or disgust towards activities or attire related to sex work.” .
.
at its best, it manifests as harmful stereotyping that lends itself to the spreading of damaging misinformation, resulting in the passing of unjust laws which only serve to push sex workers further underground. at its worst, whorephobia kills. 
_______

art [1/10] by @prdct
music by @deepsabrina
essay [1/10] by @buates.mckenzie

text:
jummah ke maukay par relevant picture se lutf andoz hoyen. 
yesterday i experienced an invigorating discussion on a ladies-in-law whatsapp group. it involved a forward regarding women of inappropriate outfits messing up aimaan of hazraat of this country and spreading lust.

my initial stance was that this is a one sided story and just because a girl walks in skinny jeans doesn't mean you pounce on her. our religion mentions pardaah for men before that of women. rape of young girls and boys happened and all we care about is what she wore? 
nobody teaches their son to rape women but hardly anyone teaches them to respect them. there is some old school romance associated with staring at a girl while she walks down the street. mix it up with screwed up upbringing and you get a harassment situation right here. whenever i talk about men discussing women and staring at them in a lewd manner i am told this is how it is. boys will be fudging boys, so guard your modesty.

i understand that. i love trends and fashion and i also use the #modestfashion hashtag, but i also dont cover my head in daily life save dangerous neighborhoods. obviously somebody will always, always disagree with your dressing.

moms, can we not teach boys not to stare? can we not teach them the #nomeansno concept? can we not create a non-judgmental situation. our own religion teaches not to judge and let ppl be, let them come to hidaayah. we shun and shame everyone but the perpetrator, the abuser.  we say, she deserved it. nobody deserves it. 
i comprehended from the discussion that safety measures are essential both for ourselves and our kids. evil exists. we need to guard against it. but are we looking for the cure in the wrong direction? we fix our dupatta but who fixes the weakened imaan of the pervert? i would love your thoughts on this.
.
.
.

text:
i wrote a paper called “women leading marches” back when i went to college. 
here’s some of the last sentences of that paper. women have been the catalyst of a lot of changes in the past few years. women in college took a stand against sexual assault on campus, challenging big universities and calling for change in the way the legal system handles such cases. hollywood women became an advocate against sexual harassment in the workplace as they, along with millions of women around the world, said #metoo. the #metoo movement changed the way our society responds to those accused of sexual assault or harassment. the women’s march was an historic event that showed the power of women across the nation and world. annually this march has continued to show the need for women’s equality. lastly a wave of women are wanting to make a difference and run for elected office. 
i’m a bit of a feminist, blame my mom.

text:
did you hear? missing teeth and 1cm bangs are all the rage for young fashionistas! 😜
•
as much as i'm disappointed with this self-given haircut, i'm also pretty proud. you see, in this house we preach about consent and being the "boss of your body."
•
we don't do forced hugs or kisses. they pick out what they wear. they are not forced to clean their plates at meals or even try everything on it. when they are taking a bath they are asked whether they want us to wash them or if they want to do it. same with toothbrushing. we don't hit them as a form of discipline. they own their bodies, and they will tell you all about it. •
cutting her own hair shows that she is taking the "boss of her body" to a whole new level. this shows autonomy. •
as much as i hate rolling into the holidays with this haircut, i'm also certain that she will have no problem telling someone "no" to a hug at holiday gatherings. that means she will have the confidence to stand up for herself and her body in the future. •
she will have years of practice being the boss of her body. boys won't have the chance to take advantage or to go too far. she is strong. she is brave. she is the boss of her body. ❤️💪

text: ❗️let op! deze blog gaat in op seksueel misbruik.❗️ikjes werd, door haar eigen ervaringen met seksueel misbruik, geraakt door de #metoo beweging. ze keurt elke vorm van seksueel misbruik sterk af, maar kreeg toch een onbehagelijk gevoel bij het feit dat alle vormen over één kam gescheerd lijken te worden en van het feit dat griet op de beeck niet geloofd werd toen ze bij dwdd vertelde dat ze door haar vader misbruikt is, omdat er geen bewijs van is. ook las ikjes dat dissociatieve identiteitsstoornissen vaak niet erkend worden, omdat “onbewuste” herinneringen vaak niet echt blijken te zijn. het wordt zelfs een ‘modeziekte’ genoemd. ‘au. blijkbaar is het fijner om te geloven dat mensen zoals ik een toneelstukje spelen, dan dat er mensen zijn die kinderen misbruiken. ik snap dat er mensen zijn die een verleden verzinnen, een stoornis faken, hier erkenning of aandacht uithalen, of zichzelf hiermee ontoerekeningsvatbaar kunnen verklaren. maar, geldt dit niet voor alle stoornissen?’ lees deze blog op dsmmeisjes.nl of via de link in bio. #dissociatieveidentiteitsstoornis #seksueelmisbruik #metoo #wetoo #endthedrama #dsmmeisjes

text:
english & dutch 👇🏼👇🏾• representation matters. in age, gender identity, ethnicity, body shape, size, and it also very much matters in (dis)ability. since i’ve started talking about my autism spectrum disorder i’ve received hundreds of messages from girls/women with autism, parents with kids on the spectrum and people (mostly women) who realize this might be the thing they’ve struggled their whole life with. they’re all different, but almost every time they share one thing: happiness about finally seeing more representation from actual autistic people. when there is no visibility of someone like you, you feel like you’re the only one out there that’s different. my first big interview in the netherlands came out this week 💕. •

hoppa! super blij met het eerste grote interview van mij in nederland, voor @evajinekofficial. ik praat onder meer over hoe autisme bij mij is gediagnosticeerd, hoe het mijn werk beïnvloedt als model wonend in new york en wat ik graag wil bereiken met het aandacht vragen voor autisme. de afgelopen anderhalf jaar heb ik namelijk veel gedeeld over mijn autisme hier op instagram, maar ook heb ik internationale interviews gedaan en artikelen geschreven zoals voor @i_d @theststyle @indiemagazine. autisme is niet los te zien van mij als persoon, en ik ben vet blij met mezelf, maar het heeft wel voor veel moeilijke momenten in mijn leven gezorgd (wat ik ook deel in het artikel). het feit dat ik nu door middel van mijn werk aandacht kan vragen voor iets dat zó dicht bij mij staat, vind ik het fijnste wat het tot dusver heeft gebracht. representatie is super belangrijk, ook als je een onzichtbare ‘handicap’ hebt, dus doe daar wat aan nederland 💫💁🏼‍♀️!! #thatskoole #autism #autisme

text:
yep that’s me!
finally a press article that is 100% factual and not sensationalising the difficult times that i went through. 
for me the whole point of my book was to live in my truth and get my readers to live in their truth. 
i’m strong enough to bat some non factual press off but that’s not the point, not everyone is! this can cause further distress. let’s not bat off lies, let’s educate our generation and generations to come to not be afraid to speak up & be in their truth because all this does is cause anyone suffering further issues and will then stop people from talking about things then need to talk about. 
it took me years to find my courage to write my story. i never set out to be an author or share my story. i just know it’s the right time and anne jirsch reminded me yesterday that if you feel it, then do it, it’s intuitive and for me opening up my life story was.

i published my self help book to give hope and inspiration to anyone going through difficult times and thus far that’s what it’s been doing, and across the globe. i’ve had many messages from people thanking me, and saying it’s given them hope and inspired them. some people have gone on to share their deepest darkest problems with not just me but loved ones. 
i would like to personally thank the henley herald for listening to me during our interview and producing this article.

also huge thanks to naz ahsun sarah parfitt julie green henley on thames susan meyers and all my friends for everything you’ve supported me with! www.emmajanetaylor.life
#author #girlboss #socialmedia #education #inspiration #timemanagement

text:
i am all for open dialogue and discussing tough topics.  i’m so ignorant about much of what’s happening in the world, i appreciate having my eyes opened to new ideas and perspectives, even if this means facing my own privilege.  as a community of people both online and in real life, communication about important issues is essential to growth and this platform is a great way to mobilize.

while i love the ability for so many people to communicate on this platform, i am not a fan of people jumping on bandwagons to bring down others.  over the past few months i’ve seen several instances in which women tear other women down.  all of this while posting #metoo and #feminist memes.  is there really a movement to support other women, or are most just waiting around for their opportunity to point the finger and participate in this destructive callout  culture that has become so popular. 
how do we really come together and support women in loving and productive ways?  we can have difficult conversations and be forced to look in the mirror, but once we start criticizing and looking for a community to join in, that’s when the growth stops and we start weakening one another. 
image for @underthehood_podcast
